No man is an island entire of itself; every man

is a piece of the continent, a part of the main;

if a clod be washed away by the sea, Europe

is the less, as well as if a promontory were, as

well as any manner of thy friends or of thine

own were; any man's death diminishes me,

because I am involved in mankind.

And therefore never send to know for whom

the bell tolls; it tolls for thee.







 No Man is an Island, by John Donne

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Nearing my third and fourth +200s (two articles at +189), I figured that I could handle a total flop if it happened. This might be a total flop. But I'm willing to take that risk. I wanted to challenge myself, so I gave myself two goals:

Post within an hour after making the first draft.
Make it the shortest mainlist SCP wordcount on the site (barring SCP-2521, that's cheating).


Hopefully this has worked.

Spoilers

Spoilers


It's a gun that kills loved ones of the target shot.








